article.headline: Fairleigh Dickinson 76, Quinnipiac 70
article.story: HACKENSACK, N.J. (AP) -- John Blackgrove's four-point play with 32 seconds remaining sparked Fairleigh Dickinson to a 76-70 win over Quinnipiac Tuesday night in the Northeast Conference opener for both teams. FDU (3-2, 1-0 NEC) led by a single point when Blackgrove nailed a fadeaway 3-pointer and converted a free throw to extend the lead to 73-68. The Knights then hit three free throws in the final 20 seconds to seal the victory. Gordon Klaiber led the Knights with 15 points, while Cameron Tyler and Andre Harris added 12 each. Chris Wehye had a game-high 19 points and 10 rebounds for the Bobcats (2-2, 0-1 NEC). John Winchester added 14 points. FDU led by as many as 14 points in the second half before an 11-1 Quinnipiac run over the final six minutes cut the margin to one before Blackgrove's clutch shot.
